column5: Here's a few pics of some cats we got this between 16-25lbs. more to come!  All released!!!
heres a couple more, more tmrw when I get my camera back

Dang!  Never caught one of those before, actually never tried, but have thought about it.  Good to know they have them in G-Bay, the question now is do they have them in my area?  I would assume so...  Thanks for the pics, amazing, Maureen
Nice Kitties!Almost had a bad typo there. Joe
Great fishing!!!!!!!!! man those are some real nice cats for sure, great pics as well...thanks for sharing   cheers
Wow chunky fish thanks for the meow mix of cats.MTP

Wow, a whole truckload of cats ...... Nice fish troutguy!  Maureen, you would have assumed right that there are nice cats in our area too. I don't want to hijack Troutguy's thread so I will send you a pm.  Tom
maureen, Im from collingwood area so these cats are local to you so to speak, great fighters and fairly simple to catch.
Nice!! I love catching big cats!!! Looks like they were in there thick!
Wow, nice 'cat'ches.  What was the bait used?
Great haul there!  I dont even know if ones that size hang around my neck of the woods...if they do, then I gotta go and get me some!!! LOL
Look at the belly on that one !!
